  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nExcept for signature verification, the only long running operation I found is `processEpoch`. It can be up to 4s-5s, exceptional ones can be up to 10s. The consequence of this is:\r\n+ Some status requests/responses are timed out at the same time\r\n+ Beacon_block_by_root, Beacon_block_by_range are timed out at the same time which cause peer score reduced\r\n+ Cannot finish handshake process with some incoming peers\r\n+ Some peers disconnect us (goodbye code = 129) because we have the worse score\r\n\r\nWhile #1464 takes the approach of using a worker thread to process state transition, we should also explore partitioning `processEpoch()` into smaller steps and make it async.\r\n\r\nhttps://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/dont-block-the-event-loop/\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nShould not make network requests/responses time out just because of long-running operations.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\nSync Medalla\r\n",
